text_logic_form: Find the perimeter of the shape.
diagram_logic_form: The length of the line $BO$ is $15$ units.
The length of the line $CO$ is $13$ units.
The length of the line $CE$ is $7$ units.
The length of the line $CO$ is equal to the length of the line $BA$.
The length of the line $BO$ is equal to the length of the line $CA$.
Point $E$ lies on the line connecting $C$ and $A$.
The line $OE$ is perpendicular to the line $EA$.

There are lines $AB$, $OE$, $CE$, forming a triangle $ABE$.
Line $AE$ is the diagonal of the parallelogram $COBA$.
